get admin url "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
=============================================================

NAME
----

get admin url - Retrieve the url to the admin area for a given site. This function is

SYNOPSIS
--------

Retrieve the url to the admin area for a given site. This function is
similar to
[admin\_url()](/Function_Reference/admin_url "Function Reference/admin url")
but includes additional support for WordPress MS.

USAGE
-----

` <?php get_admin_url( $blog_id, $path, $scheme ); ?> `

PARAMETERS
----------

 `$blog_id` 
:   ([*int*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Int "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) (optional) Blog ID. Defaults to current blog.
    Default:

 `$path` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Optional path relative to the admin url
    Default: empty string

 `$scheme` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) The scheme to use. Default is 'admin', which obeys
    force\_ssl\_admin() and is\_ssl(). 'http' or 'https' can be passed
    to force those schemes.
    Default: admin

RETURN VALUES
-------------

 `` `(string)`{style="color:gray"} 
:   Admin url link with optional path appended

CHANGE LOG
----------

Since: [3.0](/Version_3.0 "Version 3.0")

SOURCE FILE
-----------

`get_admin_url()` is located in `wp-includes/link-template.php`

